-- France, Germany Should Seek Bilateral `Convergence' on Taxes, Sarkozy Says
-- Helene Fouquet
-- 2010-07-21T10:11:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/france-germany-should-seek-bilateral-convergence-on-taxes-sarkozy-says.html

          
          
             The French and German governments
should aim for a “convergence” of their tax systems, French
President  Nicolas Sarkozy  said.  
 Sarkozy wants both countries’ national auditors to review
their tax systems in order to coordinate levies on individuals
and companies, Sarkozy said today during the weekly Cabinet
meeting, according to a statement released by his office.  
